Permissive/Interlock Release ============================================================ Instruction Overview: ----- The Permissive/Interlock instruction provides a means of collecting various digital signals into a common status bit reflecting whether or not conditions are suitable to perform a particular function. The raM_Opr_PermIntlk AOI is applicable to permissive use, where first-out capture is typically not implemented, and interlock use, where first-out capture is most likely implemented. Primary functionality: -Multi-input discrete “AND” function, solving for a single binary OK condition. -Selectable “OK” state for each enabled input. -First-out capture, with arming input. -Selectable first-out latching with reset. -Textual input identification using input element’s Logix Designer tag descriptor.
Secondary functionality: -Input bypass, allowing selected inputs to be ignored during maintenance functions.
Instruction Execution: ----- Continuous
Supplemental Descriptions: ----- Multi-Input OK Status – The raM_Opr_PermIntlk AOI base tag provides up to 32 discrete inputs that all must be in their configured state before the OK output status is set. Each of the 32 inputs can be individually enabled or disabled. The HMI faceplate provides status of each input, indicating if it is enabled or disabled, OK or not OK, or bypassed. Output OK or not OK is also indicated on the faceplate.
Selectable Input OK State – Each enabled input can be set to indicate OK when its connected signal is a 1 or a 0.
First-Out Capture – When so configured and armed, the offending inputs are captured and held when Out_OK transitions from 1 to 0.
First-Out Latching – When Cfg_ResetReqd is configured, the first-out capture must be reset from external logic or the HMI to return to normal operation. If captured and not reset, the first out condition will prevent Out_OK from being set even if all input conditions are OK or bypassed. If latching is not configured, cycling Inp_Arm to 0 then back to 1 resets the first-out capture.
Input Descriptions – Each input, Inp_00 through Inp_31, has a description string that is editable using Studio 5000 Logix Designer. These descriptions are displayed on the faceplate for the raM_Opr_PermIntlk.
Input Bypass – User can decide to bypass or normalize specific input checking from Maintenance Tab. Inp_Maint should be enabled indicating maintenance mode to allow bypass or normalize. Only those inputs will be allowed to bypass which are selected in Engineering tab. Sts_Bypassed bit indicates if any inputs are bypassed.
Revision Notes: ----- 1.0.00 - Release
